WEBVTT

1
00:01:40.579 --> 00:01:42.332
So,

2
00:01:43.233 --> 00:01:45.469
Aren't you too lazy to prepare breakfast?

3
00:01:45.469 --> 00:01:47.470
but you don't have the habit?

4
00:01:50.534 --> 00:01:52.475
I do intermittent fasting.

5
00:01:59.283 --> 00:02:01.217
It's not that you failed

6
00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:04.480
in having your license,
Did you never bother to get it?

7
00:02:06.834 --> 00:02:08.444
Well,

8
00:02:08.934 --> 00:02:11.127
It's my way of reducing
carbon emissions.

9
00:02:13.873 --> 00:02:15.632
So...

10
00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:20.003
It's not that you couldn't date, you avoided it.

11
00:02:23.440 --> 00:02:26.293
And why did you change your mind?

12
00:02:26.293 --> 00:02:28.411
You said you wanted to go slow.

13
00:02:28.946 --> 00:02:31.682
Anyone who hears you
He'll think we slept together.

14
00:02:31.682 --> 00:02:35.753
We don't sleep together,
but under the same roof.

15
00:02:35.753 --> 00:02:37.454
I think...

16
00:02:38.133 --> 00:02:40.624
meet someone

17
00:02:40.624 --> 00:02:44.828
It involves knowing your space.

18
00:02:46.847 --> 00:02:48.701
So,

19
00:02:48.701 --> 00:02:50.367
what do you think?

20
00:03:09.887 --> 00:03:12.934
I expected to see sheet music everywhere,

21
00:03:12.934 --> 00:03:15.492
that smelled like stale takeout

22
00:03:15.492 --> 00:03:17.895
and that it reeked of cigarettes.

23
00:03:17.895 --> 00:03:21.297
I thought you would live like a zombie,
that you would sleep during the day.

24
00:03:22.751 --> 00:03:24.601
Are you disappointed?

25
00:03:25.752 --> 00:03:29.606
You broke my stereotype of the musician.

26
00:03:38.653 --> 00:03:40.884
After today's tea ceremony,

27
00:03:40.884 --> 00:03:43.987
They will dine on Jeju silver scabbardfish.

28
00:03:43.987 --> 00:03:45.789
Then they will return to the hotel

29
00:03:45.789 --> 00:03:47.970
for a massage at the <i>spa</i>.

30
00:03:47.970 --> 00:03:50.373
That's today's schedule.

31
00:03:50.373 --> 00:03:54.364
Unpack and rest in your rooms.

32
00:03:54.364 --> 00:03:55.833
See you here at noon.

33
00:03:55.833 --> 00:03:56.633
See you later.

34
00:03:56.633 --> 00:03:57.835
- OK.
- Gracias.

35
00:03:57.835 --> 00:03:59.219
- Yeah.
- Gracias.

36
00:03:59.219 --> 00:04:01.204
OK. Come on.

37
00:04:05.409 --> 00:04:06.943
Sorry.

38
00:04:08.285 --> 00:04:10.485
- Do I have to go?
- Yeah.

39
00:04:10.485 --> 00:04:12.283
Sorry?

40
00:04:12.283 --> 00:04:13.883
What do you mean?

41
00:04:14.918 --> 00:04:17.487
To eat and to the excursion.

42
00:04:17.487 --> 00:04:20.123
All of that is included in the rate.

43
00:04:20.123 --> 00:04:23.693
It's a top-notch package, you'll love it.

44
00:04:24.928 --> 00:04:27.371
I prefer to rest.

45
00:04:27.371 --> 00:04:31.301
In general,
individual activities are not allowed,

46
00:04:31.301 --> 00:04:33.604
but if you stay, please,
stay at the hotel.

47
00:04:33.604 --> 00:04:37.240
We can't risk it
for you to go out and get hurt.

48
00:05:11.909 --> 00:05:15.198
[Happy 35th wedding anniversary]

49
00:05:16.359 --> 00:05:18.548
Did you sleep with him?

50
00:05:20.918 --> 00:05:24.567
You distanced yourself and played hard to get.

51
00:05:24.567 --> 00:05:27.490
We just sleep.

52
00:05:29.893 --> 00:05:31.700
I swear, we did just that. We sleep and nothing else.

53
00:05:31.700 --> 00:05:34.364
Without touching? Did they just sleep?

54
00:05:34.364 --> 00:05:36.766
- Yes.
- Is that possible?

55
00:05:38.568 --> 00:05:41.219
We decided to go slow.

56
00:05:41.219 --> 00:05:43.673
Go slow?

57
00:05:44.456 --> 00:05:47.945
The cold Seo Jun Kyung and the poor musician

58
00:05:47.945 --> 00:05:51.814
Did you agree to postpone sex?

59
00:05:53.917 --> 00:05:55.867
Well,

60
00:05:55.867 --> 00:05:57.787
Anyway, that's how it ends.

61
00:05:59.890 --> 00:06:02.896
Is this something a gynecologist should say?

62
00:06:02.896 --> 00:06:04.962
Should we encourage sex?

63
00:06:04.962 --> 00:06:07.828
There are many things you can postpone,
but just that?

64
00:06:07.828 --> 00:06:12.202
They are the laziest couple in the world.

65
00:06:12.202 --> 00:06:13.601
So,

66
00:06:13.601 --> 00:06:16.539
what did they do all night?

67
00:06:18.034 --> 00:06:19.628
Well...

68
00:06:20.834 --> 00:06:22.879
<i>we drank</i>

69
00:06:23.613 --> 00:06:25.327
<i>and we talk.</i>

70
00:06:31.567 --> 00:06:34.891
<i>He is my polar opposite,</i>

71
00:06:35.435 --> 00:06:37.727
<i>that's all I know.</i>

72
00:06:43.333 --> 00:06:45.668
<i>But somehow,</i>

73
00:06:46.236 --> 00:06:48.998
<i>that difference didn't bother me that much
like I thought it would happen.</i>

74
00:06:54.267 --> 00:06:56.112
They did it, didn't they?

75
00:06:57.446 --> 00:06:59.416
Would you believe it if someone told you?

76
00:06:59.416 --> 00:07:02.652
You can't sleep at home,
and you slept like a baby in his?

77
00:07:02.652 --> 00:07:05.588
Didn't they do anything else?

78
00:07:09.601 --> 00:07:11.269
It's true.

79
00:07:11.269 --> 00:07:12.729
How did I sleep so well

80
00:07:12.729 --> 00:07:14.764
in someone else's house?

81
00:07:37.687 --> 00:07:38.919
It doesn't matter,

82
00:07:38.919 --> 00:07:41.024
don't tell anyone.

83
00:07:41.597 --> 00:07:44.674
As if there was something to say.

84
00:07:45.564 --> 00:07:46.797
Do you know something?

85
00:07:46.797 --> 00:07:48.598
That?

86
00:07:50.801 --> 00:07:53.403
Dr. Hong didn't have lunch,
not because I'm on a diet,

87
00:07:53.403 --> 00:07:55.639
but because she had a fight with her boyfriend.

88
00:07:55.639 --> 00:07:56.873
Oh really?

89
00:07:56.873 --> 00:07:59.108
How barbaric.

90
00:08:01.011 --> 00:08:02.939
There's that smile.

91
00:08:02.939 --> 00:08:06.015
Even though it's a little uncomfortable, days have passed.

92
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:21.267
Let's eat!

93
00:08:21.267 --> 00:08:24.068
- Let's go together.
- Let's go together.

94
00:08:24.068 --> 00:08:25.702
Hurry up.

95
00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:30.740
<i>I don't have to rehearse today. Where are you?</i>

96
00:08:33.810 --> 00:08:36.045
Why are you ignoring my messages?

97
00:08:36.546 --> 00:08:38.514
You don't answer me when I call you either.

98
00:08:44.692 --> 00:08:46.856
Why are you angry?

99
00:08:47.725 --> 00:08:49.021
I'm not angry.

100
00:08:49.021 --> 00:08:50.601
So, I'm leaving.

101
00:08:50.601 --> 00:08:52.295
Wait!

102
00:08:52.963 --> 00:08:54.764
Yeah,

103
00:08:54.764 --> 00:08:56.000
I'm angry.

104
00:08:56.000 --> 00:08:57.995
What's happening? Why are you upset?

105
00:08:57.995 --> 00:09:00.137
Who is that guy?

106
00:09:00.137 --> 00:09:01.705
Who?

107
00:09:01.705 --> 00:09:03.106
That guy.

108
00:09:03.106 --> 00:09:04.741
He looks like a scoundrel.

109
00:09:04.741 --> 00:09:06.843
Post photos of yourself
on all your social networks.

110
00:09:06.843 --> 00:09:08.578
Boom Jun?

111
00:09:09.746 --> 00:09:12.048
How cute you are.

112
00:09:12.783 --> 00:09:14.517
Come here.

113
00:09:16.753 --> 00:09:18.756
What are you doing?

114
00:09:18.756 --> 00:09:20.656
Look what I do.

115
00:09:22.993 --> 00:09:25.027
"He is the light of my eyes."

116
00:09:27.464 --> 00:09:29.033
I published it.

117
00:09:29.033 --> 00:09:30.167
Are you happy now?

118
00:09:30.167 --> 00:09:31.368
- You are, right?
- No.

119
00:09:31.368 --> 00:09:33.803
Of course you are!

120
00:09:34.571 --> 00:09:35.940
Estonia?

121
00:09:35.940 --> 00:09:37.307
Have you been there?

122
00:09:37.307 --> 00:09:38.907
Yes.

123
00:09:39.392 --> 00:09:41.444
When? With who?

124
00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:45.032
Again with your suspicions.

125
00:09:45.032 --> 00:09:47.117
two years ago,
I went with my team for a show.

126
00:09:47.117 --> 00:09:48.785
I see.

127
00:09:50.409 --> 00:09:54.530
First, let's go to the most beautiful restaurant
of the historic center,

128
00:09:54.530 --> 00:09:57.460
I invite everyone I know
for the first round.

129
00:09:57.460 --> 00:09:58.595
Yes.

130
00:09:58.595 --> 00:10:01.097
Then, we go to the most popular club in the center
for the second round.

131
00:10:01.097 --> 00:10:02.545
Yes.

132
00:10:02.545 --> 00:10:04.367
And finally,

133
00:10:04.367 --> 00:10:06.068
We go back to the hotel, just you and me,

134
00:10:06.068 --> 00:10:08.970
for a suggestive third round.

135
00:10:08.970 --> 00:10:10.310
What's that?

136
00:10:10.310 --> 00:10:12.208
Well? That?

137
00:10:12.809 --> 00:10:14.311
But seriously,

138
00:10:14.311 --> 00:10:17.947
Why do you celebrate your birthday so far away?

139
00:10:19.856 --> 00:10:21.300
Well,

140
00:10:21.300 --> 00:10:23.734
It's my dream.

141
00:10:23.734 --> 00:10:25.455
Heavens.

142
00:10:25.455 --> 00:10:27.055
Hey.

143
00:10:30.126 --> 00:10:32.429
Do you want something else besides that?

144
00:10:32.429 --> 00:10:34.042
Tell me.

145
00:10:34.616 --> 00:10:36.167
If I tell you,

146
00:10:36.167 --> 00:10:37.934
will you do it?

147
00:11:00.457 --> 00:11:02.525
No!

148
00:11:47.470 --> 00:11:48.972
Hello, dad.

149
00:11:48.972 --> 00:11:50.586
<i>Hello.</i>

150
00:11:51.653 --> 00:11:53.609
I guess I shouldn't have come.

151
00:11:54.277 --> 00:11:56.412
I should have listened to Jun Seo.

152
00:12:00.002 --> 00:12:02.385
Did you go on a trip?

153
00:12:03.350 --> 00:12:05.322
<i>I'm sure you don't understand me, do you?</i>

154
00:12:05.322 --> 00:12:07.035
<i>With everything that is happening.</i>

155
00:12:10.496 --> 00:12:12.862
I felt like doing it anyway.

156
00:12:15.083 --> 00:12:16.999
I understand you.

157
00:12:21.746 --> 00:12:23.572
Have you left work yet?

158
00:12:24.475 --> 00:12:26.543
I'm on it.

159
00:12:26.543 --> 00:12:29.645
I wonder if Jun Seo is eating.

160
00:12:30.247 --> 00:12:32.139
- A party at home?
- Yes.

161
00:12:32.139 --> 00:12:35.418
I don't want a boring birthday party
in a rented room.

162
00:12:35.418 --> 00:12:37.121
I want a real birthday party.

163
00:12:37.121 --> 00:12:39.422
But my house is very small.

164
00:12:40.457 --> 00:12:41.191
What do you think?

165
00:12:41.191 --> 00:12:44.193
Your dad is away,
So there's no one home, right?

166
00:12:53.603 --> 00:12:55.139
What's happening?

167
00:12:55.139 --> 00:12:56.874
Don't you like the idea?

168
00:12:56.874 --> 00:12:58.717
It's just...

169
00:12:58.717 --> 00:13:02.212
I don't know if we should do it there.

170
00:13:02.212 --> 00:13:05.047
My mom passed away recently.

171
00:13:05.737 --> 00:13:09.586
Do you know the situation I'm going through?
at this moment.

172
00:13:09.586 --> 00:13:11.421
Yeah?

173
00:13:11.421 --> 00:13:13.824
He's not feeling well either.
and he will stay alone at home.

174
00:13:13.824 --> 00:13:16.559
It's not pleasant to eat alone.

175
00:13:17.528 --> 00:13:19.296
<i>You have to have dinner too.</i>

176
00:13:19.296 --> 00:13:21.163
Yes, and you, dad.

177
00:13:35.724 --> 00:13:37.500
I wanted to know

178
00:13:37.500 --> 00:13:39.448
if you have been able to rest.

179
00:13:40.584 --> 00:13:42.586
Yes, thanks.

180
00:13:42.586 --> 00:13:45.845
I asked at the restaurant,
They told me you didn't go to eat.

181
00:13:45.845 --> 00:13:47.724
Eating alone didn't seem right to me.

182
00:13:47.724 --> 00:13:48.859
That's right,

183
00:13:48.859 --> 00:13:51.595
That's why people gather in groups.

184
00:13:51.595 --> 00:13:54.930
I brought you abalone gimbap.

185
00:13:56.100 --> 00:13:57.685
It's for you.

186
00:14:01.137 --> 00:14:03.839
Abalone gimbap?

187
00:14:04.715 --> 00:14:07.610
Tomorrow you will be with us all day.

188
00:14:16.553 --> 00:14:19.088
I already noticed.

189
00:14:20.757 --> 00:14:23.759
Yes, it should be fine.

190
00:14:32.302 --> 00:14:33.837
OK.

191
00:14:33.837 --> 00:14:37.873
I'll put it together and ship it tomorrow morning.

192
00:14:38.742 --> 00:14:40.435
They call themselves writers,

193
00:14:40.435 --> 00:14:42.779
but the spelling mistakes
They are not something to brag about.

194
00:14:42.779 --> 00:14:44.380
Incredible.

195
00:14:53.985 --> 00:14:56.231
What pain!

196
00:14:58.762 --> 00:15:00.348
Hey.

197
00:15:01.097 --> 00:15:03.233
I'm sorry, but I have to work.

198
00:15:03.233 --> 00:15:05.334
I can't eat with you.

199
00:15:14.310 --> 00:15:16.073
Have you been to Estonia?

200
00:15:16.073 --> 00:15:18.532
I would like to go to the Baltic States.

201
00:15:18.532 --> 00:15:21.068
Someone who will go to Estonia,

202
00:15:21.068 --> 00:15:24.267
someone who is in Jeju...

203
00:15:24.267 --> 00:15:25.989
By the way,

204
00:15:25.989 --> 00:15:27.223
today is perfect

205
00:15:27.223 --> 00:15:29.300
to have a party

206
00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:31.035
on your roof

207
00:15:31.035 --> 00:15:32.895
What are you taking about?

208
00:15:38.835 --> 00:15:42.138
I feel like I'm the person
who is loneliest in the world.

209
00:16:04.275 --> 00:16:07.667
When I'm alone,
I feel this way because there is no one.

210
00:16:07.667 --> 00:16:11.234
And when I'm with someone,
also, because I fear ending up alone.

211
00:16:11.234 --> 00:16:13.022
With money or without it,

212
00:16:13.022 --> 00:16:15.137
loneliness is the same.

213
00:16:17.801 --> 00:16:20.709
Is there anything fairer than loneliness?

214
00:16:23.895 --> 00:16:25.001
No,

215
00:16:25.001 --> 00:16:26.449
It's unfair.

216
00:16:26.449 --> 00:16:30.486
I feel more alone than others,
even if it's just.

217
00:16:34.500 --> 00:16:36.792
Nobody understands me.

218
00:16:41.297 --> 00:16:43.800
I'll leave early.

219
00:16:43.800 --> 00:16:46.181
Where are you going?

220
00:16:46.181 --> 00:16:47.972
- Sorry?
- For her, it's the first day.

221
00:16:47.972 --> 00:16:50.073
You have an appointment.

222
00:16:50.073 --> 00:16:52.409
- It's a secret.
- Sure, a secret.

223
00:16:52.409 --> 00:16:54.243
Good luck.

224
00:17:00.683 --> 00:17:03.500
- Couldn't you keep the secret even for a day?
- Can!

225
00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:06.924
Don't start quietly and let it fade away.

226
00:17:06.924 --> 00:17:10.292
This time, even if you're embarrassed, do it right.

227
00:17:11.370 --> 00:17:12.495
<i>- Aunt.
- Very good.</i>

228
00:17:12.495 --> 00:17:14.897
<i>- Aunt.
- Aunt.</i>

229
00:17:14.897 --> 00:17:16.367
<i>Aunt.</i>

230
00:17:16.367 --> 00:17:18.514
<i>Come see us with your boyfriend.</i>

231
00:17:18.514 --> 00:17:21.233
<i>Come see us with your boyfriend.</i>

232
00:17:21.233 --> 00:17:24.007
<i>Come see us with your boyfriend.</i>

233
00:17:24.007 --> 00:17:27.778
Your relationship is no longer yours alone.

234
00:17:27.778 --> 00:17:30.299
Take responsibility, okay?

235
00:17:38.467 --> 00:17:40.211
Why are you looking at me like that?

236
00:17:40.211 --> 00:17:43.297
What brings you here? Without warning.

237
00:17:43.297 --> 00:17:46.511
- It's daytime. Can't I come in?
- Dad is not at home.

238
00:17:46.511 --> 00:17:48.531
He is traveling.

239
00:17:48.531 --> 00:17:49.511
I already know.

240
00:17:49.511 --> 00:17:51.033
To the side.

241
00:17:59.176 --> 00:18:01.043
Did you eat?

242
00:18:21.654 --> 00:18:25.603
Is this what you call grieving your way?

243
00:18:25.603 --> 00:18:28.203
- It's just...
- Don't say anything.

244
00:18:28.771 --> 00:18:31.173
I know what you're going to say,

245
00:18:33.895 --> 00:18:36.045
and it's probably fine.

246
00:18:40.050 --> 00:18:42.017
Thank you.

247
00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:45.988
Let's eat.

248
00:19:09.913 --> 00:19:12.620
You got a message.

249
00:19:12.620 --> 00:19:14.283
What does it say?

250
00:19:18.656 --> 00:19:20.756
It's your neighbor's.

251
00:19:25.728 --> 00:19:28.731
"Jun Kyung, today is our first day."

252
00:19:28.731 --> 00:19:32.935
"Especially during the day."
It's all I see.

253
00:19:39.842 --> 00:19:41.434
Here it is.

254
00:19:41.434 --> 00:19:44.235
Congratulations on the first day.

255
00:19:59.495 --> 00:20:02.366
Dad really knows how to make soup.
It is rich and substantial.

256
00:20:02.366 --> 00:20:03.633
It's quite conservative.

257
00:20:03.633 --> 00:20:05.634
He must have cooked it carefully, without anything strange.

258
00:20:05.634 --> 00:20:07.302
Yes.

259
00:20:11.865 --> 00:20:13.901
Do you know?

260
00:20:13.901 --> 00:20:17.679
The message that came to me...

261
00:20:18.806 --> 00:20:20.166
it's nothing...

262
00:20:20.166 --> 00:20:22.151
- Don't say it.
- That?

263
00:20:22.834 --> 00:20:24.820
I know what you're going to say,

264
00:20:26.181 --> 00:20:28.557
and it's probably fine.

265
00:20:31.934 --> 00:20:33.830
Let's eat.

266
00:20:33.830 --> 00:20:36.598
Thank you.

267
00:20:46.744 --> 00:20:48.934
How inopportune.

268
00:20:48.934 --> 00:20:50.846
What a shame.

269
00:20:59.233 --> 00:21:01.223
Yes, Do Hyun.

270
00:21:16.273 --> 00:21:18.340
What a nice place.

271
00:21:18.875 --> 00:21:22.500
What work do you do here?

272
00:21:22.500 --> 00:21:24.013
Here?

273
00:21:24.013 --> 00:21:25.567
Do you want to know

274
00:21:25.567 --> 00:21:27.801
what job

275
00:21:27.801 --> 00:21:29.551
do I do in this place?

276
00:21:39.300 --> 00:21:41.267
That?

277
00:21:41.267 --> 00:21:42.765
It's...

278
00:21:42.765 --> 00:21:43.908
Yes.

279
00:21:43.908 --> 00:21:45.634
That coffee commercial.

280
00:21:46.570 --> 00:21:49.304
It's the sequel and comes out next week.

281
00:21:52.508 --> 00:21:55.344
My music is still a draft,

282
00:21:55.344 --> 00:21:58.780
but I put it in a beautiful video.

283
00:22:03.319 --> 00:22:07.322
It's the first time I invite someone
to my studio.

284
00:22:08.324 --> 00:22:10.133
When you know me better,

285
00:22:10.133 --> 00:22:12.294
You're not going to be disappointed, right?

286
00:22:13.582 --> 00:22:15.697
Until now, no.

287
00:22:23.205 --> 00:22:26.041
What do you think of those two?

288
00:22:29.879 --> 00:22:31.601
They seem lonely.

289
00:22:31.601 --> 00:22:33.248
Well...

290
00:22:34.784 --> 00:22:36.685
I can convert them

291
00:22:37.200 --> 00:22:39.200
in a sad couple

292
00:22:39.200 --> 00:22:42.992
who senses a breakup.

293
00:22:42.992 --> 00:22:45.060
Or if I want, in a couple

294
00:22:46.300 --> 00:22:47.934
that's just starting to come out

295
00:22:47.934 --> 00:22:51.066
and feel butterflies in your stomach.

296
00:22:51.602 --> 00:22:53.492
As?

297
00:22:53.492 --> 00:22:56.004
I have that power.

298
00:22:56.004 --> 00:22:58.074
Oh really?

299
00:23:09.385 --> 00:23:12.055
It changes the vibe a lot.

300
00:23:20.096 --> 00:23:22.831
what will happen

301
00:23:23.567 --> 00:23:25.901
with those two now?

302
00:23:47.167 --> 00:23:48.991
Do you remember that...

303
00:23:49.873 --> 00:23:51.627
we agreed...

304
00:23:52.928 --> 00:23:55.998
go slow, right?

305
00:23:59.801 --> 00:24:01.470
Yes.

306
00:24:21.292 --> 00:24:23.592
Did you sleep well?

307
00:24:24.680 --> 00:24:26.697
Yes.

308
00:24:26.697 --> 00:24:28.365
Yes!

309
00:24:28.365 --> 00:24:31.500
Will you stay locked up today too?

310
00:24:31.500 --> 00:24:33.669
It's a beautiful day!

311
00:24:41.844 --> 00:24:44.632
- What an amazing place!
- I love it!

312
00:24:46.449 --> 00:24:49.286
There is little left to arrive. Hold on a little longer.

313
00:24:49.286 --> 00:24:50.919
Are you OK?

314
00:24:52.734 --> 00:24:54.589
Are you OK?

315
00:24:58.662 --> 00:25:00.529
Keep going.

316
00:25:13.143 --> 00:25:15.200
What happened?

317
00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:18.300
- Why do you stop?
- My pants tore.

318
00:25:18.300 --> 00:25:19.901
No!

319
00:25:26.122 --> 00:25:28.757
Give me that, I'll take care of it.

320
00:25:32.001 --> 00:25:33.995
Careful!

321
00:25:36.066 --> 00:25:38.300
Thank you.

322
00:25:47.977 --> 00:25:50.034
I think that jacket

323
00:25:50.034 --> 00:25:52.681
yes it helped.

324
00:25:52.681 --> 00:25:54.434
Thank goodness you brought it.

325
00:25:54.434 --> 00:25:56.318
Thank you very much, seriously.

326
00:26:01.991 --> 00:26:04.793
- Don't sit there! Burn!
- Burn!

327
00:26:08.964 --> 00:26:10.633
It's very bad.

328
00:26:10.633 --> 00:26:12.943
The owner can't do that.

329
00:26:12.943 --> 00:26:16.064
How can you change your move-in date?
When do you feel like it?

330
00:26:16.064 --> 00:26:18.803
That's the situation, what can I do?

331
00:26:18.803 --> 00:26:20.676
I must be understanding.

332
00:26:20.676 --> 00:26:23.804
They even covered the furniture deposit.
and large objects.

333
00:26:23.804 --> 00:26:25.915
There's not much left,

334
00:26:25.915 --> 00:26:27.365
that's all.

335
00:26:27.365 --> 00:26:28.385
Everything is ready.

336
00:26:28.385 --> 00:26:30.200
Don't bother

337
00:26:30.200 --> 00:26:31.921
to come back later.

338
00:26:31.921 --> 00:26:33.522
It will be faster if we do it together.

339
00:26:33.522 --> 00:26:36.145
Someone else will arrive in a while,
We will finish what is left together.

340
00:26:36.145 --> 00:26:37.701
Listen,

341
00:26:37.701 --> 00:26:40.831
Could you bring us something cool to drink?

342
00:26:40.831 --> 00:26:42.734
What do I buy?

343
00:26:42.734 --> 00:26:44.466
Whatever.

344
00:26:45.434 --> 00:26:48.103
- Be careful with traffic.
- Clear.

345
00:26:51.373 --> 00:26:54.343
They changed the date of the move,
so it will stay in someone's house.

346
00:26:54.343 --> 00:26:56.023
Won't it be uncomfortable?

347
00:26:56.023 --> 00:26:57.183
For whom?

348
00:26:57.183 --> 00:26:58.449
For him?

349
00:26:58.449 --> 00:27:00.348
Or for your feelings?

350
00:27:01.650 --> 00:27:03.744
Knowing that he is leaving suddenly makes me uneasy.

351
00:27:03.744 --> 00:27:04.944
<i>Are you leaving the country?</i>

352
00:27:04.944 --> 00:27:07.223
Are they sending him on a mission?

353
00:27:07.223 --> 00:27:08.444
Should I tell him to stay at my house?

354
00:27:08.444 --> 00:27:10.075
Are you crazy?

355
00:27:10.075 --> 00:27:12.828
You've known him for a few days,
and do you already want to live together?

356
00:27:12.828 --> 00:27:14.730
We are not going to live together,

357
00:27:14.730 --> 00:27:17.166
It will be temporary, until you move.

358
00:27:17.166 --> 00:27:19.768
That's too much. They haven't slept together yet.

359
00:27:26.008 --> 00:27:27.425
That?

360
00:27:27.425 --> 00:27:29.144
Did you sleep with him?

361
00:27:33.713 --> 00:27:35.217
<i>Even so,</i>

362
00:27:35.217 --> 00:27:38.153
you don't want

363
00:27:38.153 --> 00:27:41.346
share everything from the beginning, right?

364
00:27:41.346 --> 00:27:42.106
Seem to you?

365
00:27:42.106 --> 00:27:44.827
<i>Didn't you want to go slowly?</i>

366
00:27:44.827 --> 00:27:48.297
Bathroom habits, snoring,

367
00:27:48.297 --> 00:27:50.699
your face without makeup,
the farts you fart...

368
00:27:50.699 --> 00:27:52.468
<i>There is nowhere to hide.</i>

369
00:27:52.468 --> 00:27:56.005
In this instance,
you should just show your charming side.

370
00:27:56.005 --> 00:27:58.707
<i>You are using a risky tactic.</i>

371
00:27:58.707 --> 00:28:00.375
Yes, right?

372
00:28:05.147 --> 00:28:06.498
It seems that his assistant arrived.

373
00:28:06.498 --> 00:28:08.283
You can get off.

374
00:28:13.789 --> 00:28:15.859
That?

375
00:28:15.859 --> 00:28:17.458
<i>What's happening?</i>

376
00:28:18.896 --> 00:28:20.362
A woman came to help him.

377
00:28:20.362 --> 00:28:21.400
That?

378
00:28:21.400 --> 00:28:23.632
<i>He has longer hair than mine</i>

379
00:28:24.967 --> 00:28:27.201
and it is thinner.

380
00:28:28.667 --> 00:28:32.607
Does that mean he's staying with a woman?

381
00:28:33.310 --> 00:28:36.347
<i>Just as I thought, he is a free soul unleashed.</i>

382
00:28:36.347 --> 00:28:38.013
I have to cut.

383
00:28:47.923 --> 00:28:49.358
Looks like your helper has arrived.

384
00:28:49.358 --> 00:28:50.527
Yes.

385
00:28:50.527 --> 00:28:53.028
He went to get the last box.

386
00:28:53.555 --> 00:28:55.998
They must know each other very well.

387
00:28:55.998 --> 00:28:57.675
He is the person with whom I have the most confidence.

388
00:28:57.675 --> 00:28:59.501
We've been through everything,

389
00:29:00.302 --> 00:29:01.437
for the good and the bad.

390
00:29:01.437 --> 00:29:03.050
Do Hyun.

391
00:29:03.939 --> 00:29:05.532
Yes.

392
00:29:06.575 --> 00:29:08.243
So...

393
00:29:08.817 --> 00:29:09.812
Well...

394
00:29:09.812 --> 00:29:12.068
I brought you coffee.

395
00:29:12.068 --> 00:29:13.816
Gracias.

396
00:29:13.816 --> 00:29:15.416
Wait.

397
00:29:22.142 --> 00:29:24.192
Do you want to stay at my house?

398
00:29:26.824 --> 00:29:28.530
Of course...

399
00:29:28.530 --> 00:29:30.130
Bueno...

400
00:29:31.742 --> 00:29:33.602
I say...

401
00:29:33.602 --> 00:29:35.867
is close to move,

402
00:29:35.867 --> 00:29:37.940
the place is spacious,

403
00:29:37.940 --> 00:29:39.543
y...

404
00:29:39.543 --> 00:29:41.677
your studio is also nearby.

405
00:29:41.677 --> 00:29:43.182
OK,

406
00:29:43.182 --> 00:29:44.792
I accept.

407
00:29:46.650 --> 00:29:48.383
Oh really?

408
00:29:52.400 --> 00:29:54.491
I will introduce them.

409
00:29:54.491 --> 00:29:56.291
This is Woo Jung Hoon.

410
00:30:03.922 --> 00:30:04.933
I present to you

411
00:30:04.933 --> 00:30:06.737
a Seo Jun Kyung,

412
00:30:06.737 --> 00:30:08.137
my girlfriend

413
00:30:08.137 --> 00:30:10.007
Hello,

414
00:30:10.007 --> 00:30:12.007
Nice to meet you.

415
00:30:16.567 --> 00:30:18.380
So,

416
00:30:18.380 --> 00:30:20.200
did you believe

417
00:30:20.200 --> 00:30:23.051
What was a woman?

418
00:30:29.024 --> 00:30:31.695
What image do you have of me?

419
00:30:31.695 --> 00:30:35.830
I'm not like Hollywood musicians.

420
00:30:36.934 --> 00:30:38.233
It's just that...

421
00:30:38.233 --> 00:30:41.403
he has very silky hair

422
00:30:41.403 --> 00:30:44.939
and thin legs.

423
00:30:47.701 --> 00:30:50.301
I should invite him to lunch sometime.

424
00:30:50.301 --> 00:30:52.773
We should eat too.

425
00:30:53.840 --> 00:30:55.801
It's moving day,

426
00:30:55.801 --> 00:30:58.020
Do we have the number of a Chinese restaurant?

427
00:30:58.020 --> 00:30:59.854
Heavens!

428
00:31:03.667 --> 00:31:05.593
Thank you.

429
00:31:06.997 --> 00:31:08.897
You got jealous.

430
00:31:13.368 --> 00:31:15.603
Hang on a minute.

431
00:31:17.840 --> 00:31:19.441
Hello?

432
00:31:21.779 --> 00:31:23.681
I see.

433
00:31:23.681 --> 00:31:25.780
How often are the contractions?

434
00:31:27.583 --> 00:31:29.925
Then, we won't need oxytocin.

435
00:31:29.925 --> 00:31:31.619
I'll go right now.

436
00:31:34.858 --> 00:31:36.445
Hello, Sol.

437
00:31:36.445 --> 00:31:38.345
You said four people, right?

438
00:31:38.345 --> 00:31:39.905
Five?

439
00:31:39.905 --> 00:31:42.599
It's ok no problem.

440
00:31:42.599 --> 00:31:44.500
I already took care of everything,

441
00:31:44.500 --> 00:31:46.768
so come.

442
00:31:58.133 --> 00:31:59.814
Everything ready.

443
00:32:42.491 --> 00:32:44.826
Did you fix the pants?

444
00:32:46.962 --> 00:32:48.232
You didn't know that, did you?

445
00:32:48.232 --> 00:32:50.165
I stay next to your room.

446
00:32:54.271 --> 00:32:56.604
One moment.

447
00:33:01.793 --> 00:33:04.068
Here you go.

448
00:33:04.068 --> 00:33:05.914
Thank you so much.

449
00:33:08.784 --> 00:33:10.767
The wind in Jeju

450
00:33:10.767 --> 00:33:13.087
It's not a joke.

451
00:33:14.156 --> 00:33:16.256
Yes, I fixed the pants.

452
00:33:16.256 --> 00:33:20.161
Luckily,
They had a sewing kit in the lobby.

453
00:33:21.029 --> 00:33:22.716
Apparently, you are very skilled.

454
00:33:22.716 --> 00:33:24.106
Not really.

455
00:33:24.106 --> 00:33:26.036
I just made sure

456
00:33:26.036 --> 00:33:28.203
that it looked good so that it wouldn't be noticed.

457
00:33:32.541 --> 00:33:35.143
What will you do for dinner?

458
00:33:36.823 --> 00:33:38.477
I'll find something quick and eat here.

459
00:33:38.477 --> 00:33:41.510
Eat calmly, every meal matters.

460
00:33:41.510 --> 00:33:44.071
Try the Italian restaurant
in the Ocean Wing.

461
00:33:44.071 --> 00:33:46.054
It's pretty good.

462
00:33:48.624 --> 00:33:51.750
Do you want us to have dinner together?

463
00:33:51.750 --> 00:33:55.196
I am also alone in my free time.

464
00:34:29.166 --> 00:34:31.399
I'm not used to using cutlery.

465
00:35:02.460 --> 00:35:03.968
I saw you booked

466
00:35:03.968 --> 00:35:07.035
the yacht ride for tomorrow.

467
00:35:08.439 --> 00:35:10.040
Yes.

468
00:35:14.476 --> 00:35:17.578
I signed up because my wife
he would have loved it.

469
00:35:19.300 --> 00:35:20.948
But recently...

470
00:35:22.617 --> 00:35:24.986
passed away.

471
00:35:25.734 --> 00:35:27.330
I see.

472
00:35:28.325 --> 00:35:30.591
I wish we could have come together,

473
00:35:31.100 --> 00:35:33.161
but it was not possible.

474
00:35:35.940 --> 00:35:37.799
Still, you came.

475
00:35:41.506 --> 00:35:43.638
That's what matters.

476
00:35:48.910 --> 00:35:51.080
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

477
00:35:51.080 --> 00:35:53.181
<i>♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

478
00:35:53.181 --> 00:35:57.985
<i>♪ Happy birthday to Sol ♪
♪ Happy birthday to Sol ♪</i>

479
00:36:02.934 --> 00:36:06.227
No, please! Don't do that!

480
00:36:23.200 --> 00:36:25.012
One moment.

481
00:36:27.400 --> 00:36:29.283
Wait.

482
00:36:42.900 --> 00:36:43.933
What do they do?

483
00:36:43.933 --> 00:36:46.635
Please get out of here.

484
00:36:46.635 --> 00:36:48.269
Alright. Let's go.

485
00:36:50.034 --> 00:36:51.906
They won't allow it.

486
00:36:52.934 --> 00:36:54.601
You can't smoke here.

487
00:36:54.601 --> 00:36:56.377
They have to go out.

488
00:37:01.100 --> 00:37:03.968
What's the matter?

489
00:37:03.968 --> 00:37:05.686
Are you going to vomit?

490
00:37:27.315 --> 00:37:29.167
Thank you very much

491
00:37:29.167 --> 00:37:31.379
for today.

492
00:37:35.726 --> 00:37:37.324
Tell me...

493
00:37:39.001 --> 00:37:41.889
You didn't come with bad intentions, right?

494
00:37:42.393 --> 00:37:44.161
Sorry?

495
00:37:44.161 --> 00:37:46.194
That would worry me.

496
00:37:49.598 --> 00:37:52.567
I am a person of faith.

497
00:37:53.404 --> 00:37:54.534
So,

498
00:37:54.534 --> 00:37:56.604
there is nothing to worry about.

499
00:37:59.107 --> 00:38:01.853
Has something like this happened here?

500
00:38:01.853 --> 00:38:02.744
Sorry?

501
00:38:02.744 --> 00:38:04.702
I mean if they come to end everything.

502
00:38:05.614 --> 00:38:07.651
Yes, there was a case quite a long time ago,

503
00:38:07.651 --> 00:38:09.951
on the Camino de Santiago.

504
00:38:11.353 --> 00:38:13.353
I had a great time.

505
00:38:13.353 --> 00:38:15.556
Me too.

506
00:38:38.342 --> 00:38:40.281
<i>Call me when you're done.</i>

507
00:38:51.500 --> 00:38:52.867
Hello.

508
00:38:52.867 --> 00:38:54.930
I've finished now.

509
00:38:54.930 --> 00:38:56.564
You took too long.

510
00:38:56.564 --> 00:38:58.800
That baby owes everything to his mother.

511
00:38:58.800 --> 00:39:01.701
The birth was exhausting.

512
00:39:01.701 --> 00:39:05.001
I'm exhausted and starving.

513
00:39:05.001 --> 00:39:05.974
<i>Hurry up.</i>

514
00:39:05.974 --> 00:39:08.267
I haven't eaten yet,

515
00:39:08.267 --> 00:39:09.736
I was waiting for you for dinner.

516
00:39:09.736 --> 00:39:11.515
Haven't you eaten yet?

517
00:39:11.515 --> 00:39:13.614
You should have gone ahead.

518
00:39:15.075 --> 00:39:17.852
True, there is nothing to eat at home.

519
00:39:18.455 --> 00:39:21.692
How about those noodles?
What did we miss earlier?

520
00:39:21.692 --> 00:39:22.960
I think it's great.

521
00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:24.375
Hurry up.

522
00:39:24.375 --> 00:39:25.962
OK.

523
00:39:31.866 --> 00:39:33.901
[The neighbor]

524
00:39:40.008 --> 00:39:43.711
[Do Hyun]

525
00:40:24.806 --> 00:40:28.356
Damn, I'm hopeless.

526
00:40:53.068 --> 00:40:54.749
Thank you.

527
00:40:59.888 --> 00:41:02.390
Go ahead, I'll stay here.

528
00:41:13.334 --> 00:41:16.707
[Please make this work]

529
00:41:16.707 --> 00:41:19.607
<i>"You can survive loneliness,</i>

530
00:41:20.942 --> 00:41:23.267
<i>but still,</i>

531
00:41:23.267 --> 00:41:26.267
<i>you need someone to tell you</i>

532
00:41:26.267 --> 00:41:28.749
<i>that it's okay to be alone."</i>

533
00:41:30.888 --> 00:41:34.001
<i>Honoré de Balzac.</i>

534
00:41:34.001 --> 00:41:34.923
I'm sorry.

535
00:41:34.923 --> 00:41:37.892
<i>How is your night going?</i>

536
00:41:37.892 --> 00:41:40.767
<i>If you feel alone now,</i>

537
00:41:40.767 --> 00:41:41.963
<i>I can tell you.</i>

538
00:41:41.963 --> 00:41:43.667
It would be 9000 won.

539
00:41:43.667 --> 00:41:47.601
<i>Being alone is okay.</i>

540
00:41:55.100 --> 00:41:56.877
Did you arrive?

541
00:42:00.050 --> 00:42:01.849
You're hungry, aren't you?

542
00:42:09.133 --> 00:42:12.067
I called the washing machine technician.

543
00:42:12.067 --> 00:42:13.961
It was broken.

544
00:42:16.042 --> 00:42:18.232
<i>It was another place.</i>

545
00:42:19.033 --> 00:42:22.036
<i>My house, usually,</i>

546
00:42:24.734 --> 00:42:26.975
<i>it was gloomy,</i>

547
00:42:26.975 --> 00:42:29.546
<i>but finally he seemed to be happy...</i>

548
00:42:29.546 --> 00:42:31.345
What are you doing?

549
00:42:32.493 --> 00:42:35.850
<i>-...to see me.</i>
- Good! Good decision.

550
00:42:37.152 --> 00:42:39.286
Go wash.

551
00:42:56.640 --> 00:42:58.006
How are you doing?

552
00:42:58.006 --> 00:42:59.707
Delicious.

553
00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:04.276
Just "delicious"?

554
00:43:05.049 --> 00:43:07.040
Nothing else?

555
00:43:07.040 --> 00:43:08.883
What else?

556
00:43:10.285 --> 00:43:12.253
Well...

557
00:43:12.253 --> 00:43:14.054
Doesn't it have anything that touches your heart?

558
00:43:15.559 --> 00:43:17.525
Are you asking for compliments?

559
00:43:21.596 --> 00:43:23.831
If we were facing another dish, yes,

560
00:43:24.399 --> 00:43:25.801
but the curry is different.

561
00:43:25.801 --> 00:43:27.871
It is a comforting dish.

562
00:43:27.871 --> 00:43:29.470
Because?

563
00:43:31.206 --> 00:43:33.474
Curry is my ideal food.

564
00:43:34.232 --> 00:43:37.500
When I didn't have a penny,
I was cold and struggling as a musician,

565
00:43:37.500 --> 00:43:40.347
I had a 1000 won curry package,

566
00:43:41.218 --> 00:43:43.068
I only added potatoes and onions,

567
00:43:43.068 --> 00:43:47.422
and prepared a large quantity.

568
00:43:47.422 --> 00:43:48.667
To the second

569
00:43:48.667 --> 00:43:50.001
and on the third day,

570
00:43:50.001 --> 00:43:51.767
tasted more intense

571
00:43:51.767 --> 00:43:54.662
and, in some ways, even better.

572
00:43:58.233 --> 00:44:00.167
As if it got better overnight.

573
00:44:02.537 --> 00:44:04.973
This is how I created my fantasy.

574
00:44:04.973 --> 00:44:06.241
What fantasy?

575
00:44:06.241 --> 00:44:07.875
one night,

576
00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:10.911
I come home exhausted

577
00:44:11.467 --> 00:44:14.348
for no apparent reason.

578
00:44:16.217 --> 00:44:18.719
There she is, with her apron on,

579
00:44:19.867 --> 00:44:21.755
stirring the curry.

580
00:44:22.590 --> 00:44:24.100
That aroma invades

581
00:44:24.100 --> 00:44:26.827
the entire apartment.

582
00:44:31.310 --> 00:44:33.101
Well...

583
00:44:33.101 --> 00:44:35.002
It's a pretty simple fantasy.

584
00:44:35.703 --> 00:44:37.905
But it doesn't end there.

585
00:44:39.374 --> 00:44:41.167
He has his apron on

586
00:44:41.167 --> 00:44:44.345
and nothing more.

587
00:44:46.080 --> 00:44:47.811
- Pervert!
- You will, right?

588
00:44:47.811 --> 00:44:49.753
- I?
- Yes.

589
00:44:49.753 --> 00:44:52.119
You are crazy!

590
00:44:53.154 --> 00:44:55.634
Please make my fantasy come true.

591
00:44:55.634 --> 00:44:57.091
It's ridiculous.

592
00:45:06.534 --> 00:45:09.637
I haven't seen you laugh like that until now.

593
00:45:12.473 --> 00:45:14.609
You accompanied me so I wouldn't be locked up

594
00:45:14.609 --> 00:45:16.277
playing hard to get, right?

595
00:45:16.277 --> 00:45:18.413
Being a guide must be very hard.

596
00:45:18.413 --> 00:45:20.481
Not at all.

597
00:45:20.481 --> 00:45:22.250
I travel for free as much as I want.

598
00:45:22.250 --> 00:45:24.786
And not only that, they also pay me.

599
00:45:24.786 --> 00:45:27.655
Also, the yacht ride
It is the most expensive excursion in the package.

600
00:45:27.655 --> 00:45:29.523
Oh really?

601
00:45:38.533 --> 00:45:41.268
Being in such a beautiful place
It makes me think of my husband.

602
00:45:41.985 --> 00:45:45.526
We were never able to take a yacht trip together.

603
00:45:45.526 --> 00:45:47.125
They can still do it.

604
00:45:47.125 --> 00:45:49.576
They will have the opportunity.

605
00:45:50.611 --> 00:45:53.914
I lost my husband ten years ago.

606
00:46:08.196 --> 00:46:10.234
This doesn't know at all

607
00:46:10.234 --> 00:46:12.269
to what I eat in Seoul.

608
00:46:12.269 --> 00:46:14.099
Also try the turban snail.

609
00:46:14.099 --> 00:46:17.300
They were taken out by the <i>haenyeo</i>,
the traditional divers here.

610
00:46:33.090 --> 00:46:35.189
"Very salty."

611
00:46:35.926 --> 00:46:37.891
"Too spicy."

612
00:46:39.196 --> 00:46:41.795
My wife scolded me for it all the time.

613
00:46:43.769 --> 00:46:46.834
Now that the one who ate healthy is no longer here,

614
00:46:48.029 --> 00:46:50.237
It's funny how it works.

615
00:47:06.809 --> 00:47:08.759
Look there.

616
00:47:08.759 --> 00:47:11.717
Do you see that group?

617
00:47:11.717 --> 00:47:12.997
Yes.

618
00:47:12.997 --> 00:47:14.995
Let this stay between us, okay?

619
00:47:15.633 --> 00:47:19.150
Their treatment is somewhat different.

620
00:47:19.150 --> 00:47:21.001
Different how?

621
00:47:22.110 --> 00:47:24.550
It's the Delete It From Mind package.

622
00:47:24.550 --> 00:47:26.473
- Delete it from your mind?
- Silence.

623
00:47:29.811 --> 00:47:32.983
They look happy,

624
00:47:32.983 --> 00:47:37.317
but they are going through a bad time.

625
00:47:39.987 --> 00:47:42.023
They chose this

626
00:47:42.023 --> 00:47:44.826
just to forget about it for a while.

627
00:47:44.826 --> 00:47:46.561
When they return home,

628
00:47:46.561 --> 00:47:50.164
They will return to reality,
everything will remain exactly the same.

629
00:47:50.865 --> 00:47:53.601
But while they're here,
They want to forget everything.

630
00:47:53.601 --> 00:47:55.734
That's why

631
00:47:55.734 --> 00:47:57.238
They all wear the same hats.

632
00:47:57.238 --> 00:47:59.133
- Exact.
- I understand.

633
00:47:59.133 --> 00:48:00.701
Look.

634
00:48:00.701 --> 00:48:02.001
Do you see that couple

635
00:48:02.001 --> 00:48:03.534
of light blue shirts?

636
00:48:03.534 --> 00:48:04.312
The ones there?

637
00:48:04.312 --> 00:48:06.347
- Those who take photos.
- Yes.

638
00:48:06.347 --> 00:48:08.816
They have been married for five years.

639
00:48:08.816 --> 00:48:10.821
They both have day jobs.

640
00:48:10.821 --> 00:48:12.133
He found out

641
00:48:12.133 --> 00:48:16.224
that she was dating a co-worker.

642
00:48:16.224 --> 00:48:20.228
They fight almost every day,

643
00:48:20.228 --> 00:48:23.130
and they don't solve anything.

644
00:48:27.838 --> 00:48:29.039
See?

645
00:48:29.039 --> 00:48:31.438
They are now in "disconnect" mode.

646
00:48:33.001 --> 00:48:34.908
I see.

647
00:48:36.410 --> 00:48:38.267
Next to them,

648
00:48:38.267 --> 00:48:40.882
that man supported someone,

649
00:48:40.882 --> 00:48:44.252
He lost everything and is now broke.

650
00:48:44.252 --> 00:48:46.480
He even lost the house.

651
00:48:46.480 --> 00:48:49.265
What can you do?

652
00:48:49.265 --> 00:48:51.729
- How terrible.
- TRUE.

653
00:48:51.729 --> 00:48:53.627
It is.

654
00:48:55.897 --> 00:48:58.867
The people there,

655
00:48:58.867 --> 00:49:01.301
Do you also have stories like that?

656
00:49:01.839 --> 00:49:03.604
Exact.

657
00:49:07.391 --> 00:49:08.509
You try it.

658
00:49:08.509 --> 00:49:10.481
That? Try what?

659
00:49:10.481 --> 00:49:12.646
Try it.

660
00:49:15.634 --> 00:49:17.300
Clear.

661
00:49:17.300 --> 00:49:19.019
Let's go...

662
00:49:19.534 --> 00:49:21.355
No...

663
00:49:23.591 --> 00:49:25.311
I can't do that.

664
00:49:25.311 --> 00:49:27.794
Just say something.

665
00:49:28.465 --> 00:49:30.130
Anything works.

666
00:49:32.833 --> 00:49:34.668
That guy

667
00:49:35.667 --> 00:49:38.034
is a public official
who does office work.

668
00:49:38.034 --> 00:49:39.825
Yes.

669
00:49:39.825 --> 00:49:41.467
Recently,

670
00:49:41.467 --> 00:49:44.065
started to think

671
00:49:44.065 --> 00:49:46.914
to retire earlier.

672
00:49:47.715 --> 00:49:50.217
In fact, he resigned.

673
00:49:50.217 --> 00:49:54.955
He wanted to spend more time with his wife.

674
00:49:57.258 --> 00:49:59.259
but she

675
00:50:00.467 --> 00:50:02.629
had a serious accident

676
00:50:04.932 --> 00:50:07.205
and lost an arm.

677
00:50:07.205 --> 00:50:08.294
No!

678
00:50:08.294 --> 00:50:10.304
What an outrage.

679
00:50:15.443 --> 00:50:17.477
After the accident,

680
00:50:19.233 --> 00:50:21.682
she stopped smiling.

681
00:50:26.287 --> 00:50:28.255
I think she is convinced

682
00:50:29.790 --> 00:50:32.559
that there is no hope left.

683
00:50:36.499 --> 00:50:38.298
He has been providing...

684
00:50:39.434 --> 00:50:41.400
your time,

685
00:50:41.400 --> 00:50:43.637
your heart,

686
00:50:44.273 --> 00:50:46.807
everything to her.

687
00:50:48.634 --> 00:50:51.211
But it's sold out.

688
00:50:53.614 --> 00:50:56.483
Sometimes you don't see the time

689
00:50:57.073 --> 00:50:59.720
for everything to end.

690
00:51:02.440 --> 00:51:06.159
Then he hates himself for thinking that.

691
00:51:08.095 --> 00:51:11.467
And the reason he traveled alone is...

692
00:51:11.467 --> 00:51:13.166
Well...

693
00:51:21.549 --> 00:51:23.177
He doesn't appear to have anything on his arm.

694
00:51:23.177 --> 00:51:24.774
Sorry?

695
00:51:28.816 --> 00:51:32.419
No one knows he uses a prosthetic arm.

696
00:51:33.320 --> 00:51:34.987
His arm itches.

697
00:51:34.987 --> 00:51:38.725
You still have the feeling that it is itchy.

698
00:51:41.392 --> 00:51:43.400
Did you write this for me to read?

699
00:51:43.400 --> 00:51:44.699
Sorry?

700
00:51:44.699 --> 00:51:46.700
Don't you hear how it sounds?

701
00:51:48.606 --> 00:51:50.771
That is,

702
00:51:50.771 --> 00:51:52.834
We have already passed the stage of stupidity.

703
00:51:52.834 --> 00:51:54.508
If you had used your phone

704
00:51:54.508 --> 00:51:56.577
or you would have tried a little,

705
00:51:56.577 --> 00:52:00.047
You wouldn't have delivered something like that.

706
00:52:01.434 --> 00:52:02.783
Do you know?

707
00:52:02.783 --> 00:52:05.119
They all got jobs
after graduating,

708
00:52:05.119 --> 00:52:08.556
but you came to university
as if they had a great vocation.

709
00:52:08.556 --> 00:52:10.701
Honestly, I don't care.

710
00:52:10.701 --> 00:52:12.105
Yeah?

711
00:52:12.105 --> 00:52:15.996
Do you care about your life and where you are going?

712
00:52:18.489 --> 00:52:21.301
If you cared, you wouldn't do this.

713
00:52:21.845 --> 00:52:25.339
But to your poor parents
They must care a lot.

714
00:52:28.209 --> 00:52:29.214
Heavens...

715
00:52:29.214 --> 00:52:32.779
you have no idea
that the only one who ruins your life is you.

716
00:52:33.350 --> 00:52:35.882
Poor.

717
00:52:43.367 --> 00:52:45.235
He's an idiot,

718
00:52:45.726 --> 00:52:47.544
Now you're bringing my parents into this?

719
00:52:47.544 --> 00:52:50.431
Who does he think he is?

720
00:52:50.431 --> 00:52:52.032
Why don't you say it to his face?

721
00:52:52.032 --> 00:52:55.125
This is disrespectful.
It is abuse of power by the teacher.

722
00:52:55.125 --> 00:52:56.434
And?

723
00:52:56.434 --> 00:52:58.271
Are you going to sue him?

724
00:53:01.478 --> 00:53:03.083
No.

725
00:53:03.714 --> 00:53:06.313
I will rewrite it and send it to you again.

726
00:53:07.084 --> 00:53:08.749
Good.

727
00:53:13.320 --> 00:53:15.923
When will I meet your boyfriend?

728
00:53:15.923 --> 00:53:17.424
Why now?

729
00:53:17.424 --> 00:53:20.128
Shouldn't they make it public now?

730
00:53:20.128 --> 00:53:22.484
They had to make it official with everyone.

731
00:53:22.484 --> 00:53:23.844
Now they live together.

732
00:53:23.844 --> 00:53:26.400
I already told you that we are not living together.

733
00:53:33.541 --> 00:53:34.678
Aren't you going out?

734
00:53:34.678 --> 00:53:36.376
Answer.

735
00:53:40.681 --> 00:53:42.043
Hello, Do Hyun.

736
00:53:42.043 --> 00:53:43.843
<i>You're done, right?</i>

737
00:53:43.843 --> 00:53:45.457
<i>What are we doing for dinner?</i>

738
00:53:45.457 --> 00:53:46.278
For dinner?

739
00:53:46.278 --> 00:53:48.389
Hyeong Jun will do <i>dakbokkeumtang</i>.

740
00:53:48.389 --> 00:53:51.325
What do you think?

741
00:53:51.325 --> 00:53:53.038
<i>- Excuse me?</i>
- No, he...

742
00:53:53.038 --> 00:53:54.862
Let's eat together!

743
00:53:54.862 --> 00:53:57.431
- Hey.
- I'd love to.

744
00:53:57.431 --> 00:53:58.917
Alright?

745
00:53:58.917 --> 00:54:00.838
Don't feel pressured to accept.

746
00:54:00.838 --> 00:54:02.602
He's not a very good cook.

747
00:54:03.968 --> 00:54:05.206
Lee Yeon, Ian,

748
00:54:05.206 --> 00:54:07.110
come eat

749
00:54:36.036 --> 00:54:39.707
Jun Kyung hasn't dated anyone in years.

750
00:54:39.707 --> 00:54:42.567
Sometimes she feels like she is our oldest daughter,

751
00:54:42.567 --> 00:54:44.845
so I'm very happy.

752
00:54:47.000 --> 00:54:48.782
So you make music.

753
00:54:49.266 --> 00:54:50.584
Yes.

754
00:54:50.584 --> 00:54:52.389
What kind of music do you make?

755
00:54:54.079 --> 00:54:57.924
I don't stick to a specific genre.

756
00:54:59.260 --> 00:55:03.286
So, do you busk?

757
00:55:04.520 --> 00:55:05.699
Well...

758
00:55:05.699 --> 00:55:07.741
I compose music for films and videos.

759
00:55:07.741 --> 00:55:10.903
For videos.

760
00:55:11.438 --> 00:55:14.575
Something we can recognize?

761
00:55:14.575 --> 00:55:17.310
Tell us what you have done.

762
00:55:19.534 --> 00:55:21.281
Anything you know?

763
00:55:22.219 --> 00:55:23.317
Well...

764
00:55:23.317 --> 00:55:24.752
It doesn't have to be famous.

765
00:55:24.752 --> 00:55:27.654
Tell us anything you've done.
We will look for it.

766
00:55:28.889 --> 00:55:30.557
Let's see...

767
00:55:32.267 --> 00:55:33.894
how about this one?

768
00:55:34.467 --> 00:55:36.162
Let's see if you know him.

769
00:55:46.674 --> 00:55:48.408
I know him.

770
00:55:56.601 --> 00:55:58.185
This one has animals, right?

771
00:55:58.185 --> 00:56:01.054
They just met.
How come they are already such friends?

772
00:56:03.193 --> 00:56:05.191
Look at you.

773
00:56:05.829 --> 00:56:07.427
That?

774
00:56:08.614 --> 00:56:10.801
They barely know each other.

775
00:56:10.801 --> 00:56:12.899
Do you like it that much?

776
00:56:14.204 --> 00:56:15.969
Yes I like it.

777
00:56:18.175 --> 00:56:20.601
Maybe I got too excited.

778
00:56:20.601 --> 00:56:23.210
It's not that attractive

779
00:56:23.210 --> 00:56:27.151
nor does he have a statuesque physique.

780
00:56:27.151 --> 00:56:29.225
So what did you see in him?

781
00:56:29.225 --> 00:56:32.906
Why does our worldly and cold Jun Kyung

782
00:56:32.906 --> 00:56:35.021
fell exhausted?

783
00:56:41.699 --> 00:56:43.764
Just because.

784
00:56:43.764 --> 00:56:45.001
Just because?

785
00:56:45.001 --> 00:56:46.133
Yeah.

786
00:56:46.133 --> 00:56:47.723
I like it.

787
00:56:54.878 --> 00:56:55.809
Have a good trip.

788
00:56:55.809 --> 00:56:57.111
- I close the door.
- Bye bye.

789
00:56:57.111 --> 00:56:58.409
Hyeong Jun.

790
00:56:58.409 --> 00:56:59.780
You remember what I said, right?

791
00:56:59.780 --> 00:57:01.881
Yes, I remember.

792
00:57:02.453 --> 00:57:03.450
Goodbye, Jun Kyung.

793
00:57:03.450 --> 00:57:04.250
Bye bye.

794
00:57:04.250 --> 00:57:06.019
Goodbye, Do Hyun.

795
00:57:12.960 --> 00:57:14.570
So?

796
00:57:16.230 --> 00:57:18.335
I am opposed to this relationship.

797
00:57:18.335 --> 00:57:19.503
Because?

798
00:57:19.503 --> 00:57:22.235
You got along well with Do Hyun.

799
00:57:24.242 --> 00:57:26.306
He's too good for her,

800
00:57:27.077 --> 00:57:29.476
It's a waste that he's with Jun Kyung.

801
00:57:29.476 --> 00:57:32.598
Honestly, I don't like it either.

802
00:57:32.598 --> 00:57:34.078
Because?

803
00:57:34.078 --> 00:57:35.534
Because now,

804
00:57:35.534 --> 00:57:38.085
When something fun happens,

805
00:57:38.085 --> 00:57:41.335
He'll tell Do Hyun first, not me.

806
00:57:41.335 --> 00:57:45.058
<i>And when things go wrong,
will lean on Do Hyun.</i>

807
00:57:50.162 --> 00:57:52.032
<i>To be honest,</i>

808
00:57:52.801 --> 00:57:54.768
<i>I was afraid.</i>

809
00:57:55.306 --> 00:57:56.970
<i>About what?</i>

810
00:58:00.441 --> 00:58:03.781
Not fitting in with someone like him

811
00:58:03.781 --> 00:58:06.446
or that he didn't want to fit in with me.

812
00:58:09.486 --> 00:58:11.518
Haven't I changed much?

813
00:58:12.622 --> 00:58:14.421
No.

814
00:58:14.961 --> 00:58:17.594
You've always been like this.

815
00:58:17.594 --> 00:58:20.560
You just went back to being Seo Jun Kyung.

816
00:58:24.992 --> 00:58:26.615
Oh really?

817
00:58:31.238 --> 00:58:32.841
What are you doing?

818
00:58:33.344 --> 00:58:35.442
You haven't even changed.

819
00:58:39.079 --> 00:58:41.484
It's time to sleep,
and I'm getting drunk.

820
00:58:42.716 --> 00:58:46.019
I think I got too excited today.

821
00:58:50.873 --> 00:58:54.127
I think today will stay with me for a while.

822
00:58:56.109 --> 00:58:58.899
It was such a good day

823
00:58:58.899 --> 00:59:02.035
that I almost feel like I don't deserve it.

824
00:59:10.434 --> 00:59:12.312
In fact...

825
00:59:14.534 --> 00:59:17.784
My mom passed away recently.

826
00:59:34.196 --> 00:59:35.969
I'm sorry, I didn't know.

827
00:59:58.400 --> 01:00:01.227
I look a lot like my mom.

828
01:00:03.795 --> 01:00:05.965
But, in recent times,

829
01:00:07.768 --> 01:00:10.236
we get to feel

830
01:00:11.104 --> 01:00:13.072
<i>a great resentment.</i>

831
01:00:21.148 --> 01:00:23.483
I couldn't even tell him

832
01:00:24.601 --> 01:00:26.519
that I felt it.

833
01:00:29.567 --> 01:00:31.624
We did not reconcile.

834
01:00:34.134 --> 01:00:36.196
She left.

835
01:00:48.233 --> 01:00:50.810
Even if you never told him...

836
01:00:53.701 --> 01:00:56.249
just the fact of having...

837
01:01:00.334 --> 01:01:03.423
that feeling,

838
01:01:03.423 --> 01:01:05.567
